Pre-Game Insights: The Gambia will on Sunday 8th September 2024 host Tunisia in a must win match of the 2025 Total Energies Africa Cup of Nations qualifier.
Captain Omar Colley and goalkeeper Ebrima Jarju are both ready for the match after missing the previous qualifier against Comoros Islands due to late arrival.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match will be held at the Stade El Abdi Jadida in Morocco at 4pm.
The Gambia must defeat Tunisia to increase their chances of qualifying for the 2025 Total Energies Africa Cup of Nations.
In the 2021 Total Energies Africa Cup of Nations, The Gambia defeated Tunisia 1-0.
